body_html:
I have just confirmed that the original readme is correct.
Maybe we had a bad release which you saw the issue?
Or is it possible maybe on windows our API is messed up somehow?

>>> tf.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'python'
>>> tf.contrib.tfprof.ProfileContext
<class 'tensorflow.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext'>
>>> tf.__version__
'1.4.0'

Therefore, I will close this PR. Thank you very much for the proposed fix, and if you can find the root cause of the issue, I am happy to work with you to fix the issue on our end.

body:
I have just confirmed that the original readme is correct.
Maybe we had a bad release which you saw the issue?
Or is it possible maybe on windows our API is messed up somehow?
```
>>> tf.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: 'module' object has no attribute 'python'
>>> tf.contrib.tfprof.ProfileContext
<class 'tensorflow.python.profiler.profile_context.ProfileContext'>
>>> tf.__version__
'1.4.0'
```

Therefore, I will close this PR. Thank you very much for the proposed fix, and if you can find the root cause of the issue, I am happy to work with you to fix the issue on our end.
